 categories of gift, care, money, and transparency, shifting attention away from material transactions by prioritizing relations and practices that transcend economic rationality. At a time when health care reforms and the costs of care are being widely debated, this book is a contribution to the larger discussion about the ethics and future of health care around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aExchangexSocial aspectszLithuania. 0aMedical care, Cost ofxSocial aspectszLithuania. 0aMedical economicsxMoral and ethical aspectszLithuania. 0aMedical economicsxSocial aspectszLithuania. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aSoviet & East European History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Physical.2bisacsh  agifts to medical practitioners, corruption in lithuanian health care, health care and post socialist capitalism, medical culture in lithuania.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501766084?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501766084423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501766084/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE